newsitem.title: USA: U.S. SOYBEAN WEEKLY EXPORT SALES HIGHLIGHTS--USDA.
newsitem.headline: U.S. SOYBEAN WEEKLY EXPORT SALES HIGHLIGHTS--USDA.

text.p: USDA soybean export sales highlights in latest reporting week:
Sales of 405,400 MT were three and one-quarter times the previous week and three and two-fifths times the 4-week average.

Major increases were for the Netherlands (98,500 MT), unknown destinations (84,500 MT), Mexico (55,900 MT), and Germany (54,000 MT). Sales of 295,600 MT for delivery during the 1997/98 marketing year were primarily the result of increases for Germany (173,000 MT), Mexico (54,200 MT), the Netherlands (35,400 MT), and Japan (25,300 MT) being partially offset by reductions for China (47,500 MT, including new sales of 55,000 MT and cancellations of 102,500 MT).

Exports of 161,700 MT were 9 percent above the previous week and 16 percent more than the 4-week average. The primary destinations were China (57,700 MT), Mexico (41,300 MT), and Venezuela (20,600 MT).
